    <text id="F1106T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Freedley tells Dr. Hiester about the leg wound that he received at the battle of
                    Gettysburg.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
               

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-07-19">July 19<hi rend="super">
                                <hi rend="underline">th</hi>
                        </hi> 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Gettysburg <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Penn</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Doctor</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have been dangerously wounded in the battle of the 2<hi rend="super">
                        <add hand="h1" place="inline">d</add>
                    </hi>
                    <abbr expan="instant">inst</abbr> I am as yet unable to be moved I am shot in
                    the left knee. The wound is a serious one and will deprive me of the use of the
                    joint for a long time if the joint is not altogether destroyed I am at the house
                    of D Wills <abbr expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr> and receive every attention<pb n="2"
                    /></p>
                <p>Write to me here I fear we will never play billiards together again.</p>
                <p>I have written to you several times but presume you did not know where to reply.</p>
                <p>Remember me kindly to Maria &amp; Mr Hiester</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>H W Freedley</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P.S. Do not let Maria know I am so badly wounded</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
